Na5 {transposes to 6.d3}) 8... Na5 $1 {On the other hand, exchanging the
powerful b3-bishop makes Black's play much easier, as usual.} 9. Nxe7 Qxe7 10.
d4 ({The modest} 10. d3 h6 11. Bd2 Nxb3 12. axb3 O-O $11 {doesn't pose Black
any problems either.}) 10... h6 (10... O-O 11. Bg5 h6 12. Bh4 {isn't bad for
Black either, but in this case White's setup looks more active.}) 11. Re1 O-O
12. Bd2 Nxb3 13. axb3 Bb7 ({Good enough was also} 13... c5 $5 14. d5 Nh7 $132 {
, followed by f7-f5.}) 14. d5 Nd7 15. g3 $6 ({Better was} 15. c4 f5 16. exf5
Rxf5 17. Nd4 Rf7 {with mutual chances.}) 15... f5 {Black seized the initiative
