19. g4 ({After} 19. Nxc4 Bxf3 20. gxf3 Nxc4 21. Qxc4 Qa5 22. Be3 Rbc8 23. Qe2
Qh5 {Black has sufficient counter-play on the kingside.}) 19... Bg6 20. Nxc4
Nxc4 21. Qxc4 Rc8 22. Qe2 Re8 $44 {Black's compensation is undeniable.}) 14...
c5 {At this turn, Black starts his usual expansion on the queenside.} 15. Ng3
Bg6 16. Nh4 {Eventually White acquires the bishop pair, but it diminishes his
