dxe5 14. d6 $14)) 12. Nbd2 ({The other popular choice is} 12. h3 Bd7 13. Nbd2 (
13. Bg5 {The idea behind this move is to exchange the Nf6, that would diminish
Black's control of d5. However, the desertion of the bishop of queenside might
backfire.} c6 14. dxc6 Qxc6 15. Nbd2 (15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Qd3 Nc4 17. b3 Nb6 {
was clearly better for Black in Ezhov,S - Bencheikh,I FICGS email 2011}) 15...
h6 16. Bh4 ({More to the point was} 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. b4 Nb7 18. Re3 {,
